{"tmdb_id":133960,"name":"Animusic","original_name":"Animusic","first_air_date":"2001-06-23","overview":"Animusic is an American company specializing in the 3D visualization of MIDI-based music. Founded by Wayne Lytle, it is incorporated in New York and has offices in Texas and California. The initial name of the company was Visual Music, changed to Animusic in 1995.\n\nThe company is known for its Animusic compilations of computer-generated animations, based on MIDI events processed to simultaneously drive the music and on-screen action, leading to and corresponding to every sound.\n\nUnlike many other music visualizations, the music drives the animation. While other productions might animate figures or characters to the music, the animated models in Animusic are created first, and are then programmed to follow what the music \"tells them\" to. 'Solo cams' featured on the Animusic DVD shows how each instrument actually plays through a piece of music from beginning to end.","poster_path":"/cXhAeaGd0FO7zPBpJS4NFwBzbKm.jpg","backdrop_path":"/l0Xyf5LmC3QGszrxmvcKtZrxuKp.jpg","status":"Ended","number_of_seasons":3,"vote_average":10.0,"vote_count":2,"original_language":"en","genres":["Animation"],"slug":"animusic-133960","trailers":[{"youtube_id":"rGCTLJDoMGw","title":"\"Harmonic Voltage\" - Animusic.com","trailer_type":"clip","language":"en","region":"US","is_official":false,"published_at":"2009-04-24T05:13:05.000Z","quality":480},{"youtube_id":"2lExkQMEHhU","title":"Animusic - Pipe Dream 2 - Bonus Feature","trailer_type":"clip","language":"en","region":"US","is_official":false,"published_at":"2008-08-12T21:39:20.000Z","quality":480},{"youtube_id":"XBOQcQO0IFI","title":"\"Starship Groove\" - Animusic.com","trailer_type":"clip","language":"en","region":"US","is_official":false,"published_at":"2008-03-28T21:10:54.000Z","quality":360},{"youtube_id":"toXNVbvFXyk","title":"\"Resonant Chamber\" - Animusic.com","trailer_type":"clip","language":"en","region":"US","is_official":